This paper is about top-$N$ recommender systems, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) in computer science. The paper proposes a method for utilizing high-dimensional side information, which involves feature selection and optimization. This aligns with the topics covered in machine learning (LG), artificial intelligence (AI), and statistical learning (SI) subcategories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques such as augmented Lagrange multiplier and alternating direction method, which are relevant to the optimization (DS) subcategory.
